-- Jefferies Group Hires McGinley in Expansion of Its Municipal-Bond Trading
-- Allison Bennett
-- 2010-06-15T21:18:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/jefferies-group-hires-mcginley-in-expansion-of-its-municipal-bond-trading.html

          
          
             Jefferies Group Inc.  hired  Barclays
Plc’s   James McGinley  as a managing director and head of
municipal securities markets, as it expands trading in the $2.8
trillion market for state and local government debt.  
 “We are still hiring,” said Kenneth Gibbs , president of
the municipal division of New York-based Jefferies in an e-mail.
“We see further opportunity in the market.”  
 McGinley has worked in the municipal debt market for 20
years, the company said today in a release. He was most recently
a managing director at Barclays Capital Inc., where he ran
municipal high-grade, taxable and proprietary trading as well as
competitive bidding. He has also worked at Bear Stearns Asset
Management, Blackrock Advisors Inc. and Prudential Securities.  
 At Jefferies & Co., where there are more than 90 people in
the municipal department, McGinley will work with  Alan Greco ,
head of municipal trading, and  Drew Levinson , head of municipal
sales, according to the release.  
